<h2>Make a Donation to the Victorian Web</h2> 

<img src="../icons2/vntop.gif"/>

<p class="bc">
[<a href ="../index.html">Victorian Web Home</a> â€”> 
<a href="bequests.html">Bequests</a> ]
</div>

<div id="main">

<a href="https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/952cfd33-9bad-4699-81ba-60788635cc28"
target="new">
<img src="donate.jpg" alt="donate button" height="100" border="0" class="floatright"></a>

<p class="one">The <span class="website">Victorian Web</span> 
relies on its readers for essential financial support. <b>
Please consider <a
href="https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/952cfd33-9bad-4699-81ba-
60788635cc28" target="new">
making a donation</a> today -- your support is crucial to our mission.</b> 
All gifts, no matter how large or small, are welcome.</p>

<p class="lq">Donations may be made via direct debit/ACH, credit card,
Apple Pay, and Google Pay. If you would prefer to write a
check, contact the Treasurer, Noah Landow, at <a href="mailto:finance@victorianweb.org">
finance@victorianweb.org</a>
to make arrangements.</p>

<p>Founded in 1987 by <a href="https://victorianweb.org/cv/gplbio.html">George P. Landow</a> 
at Brown University in Providence, Rhode Island, the <span class="website">Victorian
Web</span> is the internet's oldest and largest website devoted to Victoriana. The site
contains more than one hundred thousand documents and attracts thousands of 
vistors per month. Primarily staffed by volunteers, the <span class="website">Victorian
Web</span> relies on donations to stay afloat. Your tax-deductible gift
helps us to cover our operational expenses -- website hosting, site
maintenance, and some editorial help.</p>

<p class="lq">You can access our online donation page <a
href="https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/952cfd33-9bad-4699-81ba-
60788635cc28" target="new">here</a>, or by clicking the "Donate" button
at top right. 
 </p>

<p>While the majority of our donations are one-time contributions,
we sometimes hear from those who wish to contribute in a more enduring way. 
Remembering the <span class="website">Victorian Web</span> in your will is a wonderful way to make
a lasting contribution. If you are considering a bequest, please contact
Noah Landow, Treasurer, at <a href="mailto:finance@victorianweb.org">finance@victorianweb.org</a> 
for simple instructions. Learn more
 about <a href="bequests.html">making a bequest</a> to the <span class="website">Victorian Web</a>.</p>

<p>The Victorian Web Foundation 
is a registered 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. 
Contributions are tax-deductible to the extent permitted by law.
Our tax identification number is 84-5014830. 
</p>



